## Auto-trigger: academic-writing

> **Auto-trigger.** If the user's message contains any of `report`, `writeup`, `write up`, `documentation`, `paper`, `draft`, `progress note`, `progress update` AND the implied output is longer than ~30 lines of prose, also load and apply `academic-writing.mdc` from this same workspace. Treat the output as report-grade IMRaD (Abstract → Introduction → Related Work → Methodology → Implementation → Results → Discussion → Conclusion → References) with the LaTeX-canonical / DOCX-editable workflow per `latex-docx-workflow.md`. The Related Work section requires a real literature search step (see `literature-review-protocol.md`) — no hand-waving with fabricated citations. The Methodology and Results follow `readability-and-clarity.md`. Do NOT substitute a vanilla Markdown summary unless the user explicitly says "quick note" or "summary only" or "TL;DR".

